“Based on the latest data, our team of experts now agrees that we can begin the next front in our war, which we’re calling, ‘Opening up America again,’” Trump said.
He said the plan is based on “hard, verifiable data” and that the peak death rate from the disease is now behind us.
The National Coronavirus Recovery Commission, a project of The Heritage Foundation, is gathering America’s top thinkers together to figure that out.
The panel is working to provide recommendations to federal, state, and local governments, as well as to the private sector.
Vice President Mike Pence said the phased approach will focus on preventing recurrence of the coronavirus in states where it has declined.